{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Slavic words ''beli'' or ''beo'', meaning ''white'' and ''[[grad]]'' meaning ''city'' or ''town''. It was named after the white wall of the fortress that enclosed the city.

===Proper noun===
'''Belgrade'''

# The capital of [[Serbia and Montenegro]] and capital of the constituent republic of [[Serbia]], and of former [[Yugoslavia]].

